goals.question: What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of Date vs CO2
goals.rationale: This visualization will show how the CO2 concentration has changed over time and if there is any seasonality or trend in the data.

goals.question: What is the distribution of CO2 concentration?
goals.rationale: This visualization will show the frequency distribution of CO2 concentration and if there are any outliers or unusual patterns in the data.

goals.question: What is the relationship between CO2 and adjusted CO2?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of CO2 vs adjusted_CO2
goals.rationale: This visualization will show if there is any correlation between CO2 and adjusted CO2 and if the two variables are measuring the same thing.

goals.question: What is the average CO2 concentration by month?
goals.visualization: bar chart of Month vs CO2
goals.rationale: This visualization will show if there is any seasonality in the CO2 concentration and if there are any months with significantly higher or lower CO2 concentration.

goals.question: What is the distribution of the difference between CO2 and adjusted CO2?
goals.rationale: This visualization will show if there is any systematic difference between CO2 and adjusted CO2 and if the adjustment process is working correctly.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='Date', y='CO2', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?', wrap=True)
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['CO2'] = pd.to_numeric(data['CO2'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='CO2', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean CO2: {:.2f}'.format(data['CO2'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='CO2', y='adjusted_CO2', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between CO2 and adjusted CO2?', wrap=True)
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['Month'] = data['Date'].dt.month_name()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='Month', y='CO2', data=data, ci=None)
    chart.axhline(y=data['CO2'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean CO2 concentration')
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average CO2 concentration by month?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['CO2_diff'] = data['CO2'] - data['adjusted_CO2']
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='CO2_diff', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['CO2_diff'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'mean={data["CO2_diff"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the difference between CO2 and adjusted CO2?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
